//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_roster}

NOTE: This operation rosters
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account_s}
in the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission.
Read-only observation: lists all SAs, filters to director-prefixed emails, and emits one fact per discovered SA via
{buf_write_fact_multi}
against the `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` extension constant.
Fact value is the full SA email; `file_root` is the bare identity extracted from the email.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` from the resulting access token

//axhos_step
. *List service accounts*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCOUNTS»` from response `.accounts[]` array

//axhos_step
. *Filter to director service accounts*:
.. From `«ACCOUNTS»`, read the `.email` field of each entry and test whether it matches `^${RBCC_account_director}-(.+)@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}$`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_EMAILS»` — the matching emails; per-role observation per BBAAQ contract

//axhos_step
. *Emit Fact Per Discovered {rbtr_director}*:
.. For each `«SA_EMAIL»` in `«DIRECTOR_EMAILS»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«IDENTITY»` from the regex capture group — the portion of `«SA_EMAIL»` between `${RBCC_account_director}-` and `@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}`
... {rbbc_call}
{buf_write_fact_multi}
with three positional arguments:
.... `<file_root>`: `«IDENTITY»` (bare identity — the basename root for the emitted fact file)
.... `<ext>`: `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` (resolves at source time to `roster-director`)
.... `<value>`: `«SA_EMAIL»` (the full service account email address)

//axhos_step
. *Report count*:
.. {rbbc_show}
total count of emitted director fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution rosters {rbtr_director} service accounts via per-SA fact emission — one `roster-director` fact file per discovered identity, each containing the full SA email as its value.
The operation is read-only; no service accounts are created or modified.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

NOTE: This operation mirrors upstream tool images (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft, binfmt, skopeo) into a datestamped GAR namespace within the
{rbtgi_depot}.
The resulting reliquary is referenced by vessel regimes via `RBRV_RELIQUARY` and consumed at conjure time as the toolchain source.

The
{rbtr_director}
inscribes a reliquary:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Derive Reliquary Datestamp*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARY»` as `r` + `YYMMDDHHMMSS` from current time
.. Example: `r260415120000`

//axhos_step
. *Submit Inscribe Cloud Build*:
.. Construct Build resource JSON with:
... step image: `gcr.io/cloud-builders/docker` (Google-hosted, always pullable)
... step script: `rbgji01-inscribe-mirror.sh` (docker pull/tag/push per tool image)
... substitutions: `_RBGN_GAR_HOST`, `_RBGN_GAR_PATH`, `_RBGN_RELIQUARIES_ROOT`, `_RBGN_RELIQUARY`
... resulting tool image path shape: `${_RBGN_GAR_HOST}/${_RBGN_GAR_PATH}/{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/${_RBGN_RELIQUARY}/<tool>:${_RBGN_RELIQUARY}` (both path segment and tag are the reliquary datestamp, per the categorical layout)
... serviceAccount:
{rbtr_mason}
... pool: tethered (upstream pull requires public egress)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/create[builds.create] with:
... project:
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... location:
{rbrd_gcp_region}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_ID»` from response `.metadata.build.id`
.. {rbbc_show}
build dispatched with `«BUILD_ID»`
.. {rbbc_show}
Cloud Console URL for build monitoring

//axhos_step
. *Wait for Build Completion*:
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/get[cloudbuild.builds.get] for `«BUILD_ID»`
.. Poll at 5-second intervals for up to 120 attempts (~10 minutes)
.. {rbbc_require}
final status is `SUCCESS`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbf_fact_reliquary}
. *Write Fact File*:
.. {rbbc_store}
{rbf_fact_reliquary}
with value `«RELIQUARY»`

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution mirrors all tool images into the reliquary namespace.
Set `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«RELIQUARY»` in vessel {rbrv_regime} files to use this reliquary for subsequent conjure operations.

